org.openbel.framework.core.protocol.handler
Class FTPConnector

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.core.protocol.handler.FTPConnector

public class FTPConnector
extends Object

FTPConnector implements the ftp client connector which is responsible for:

  • authenticating with the ftp server
  • retrieves a file from the connected ftp server

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

retrieveFile

public void retrieveFile(String remotePath,
                         String localPath)
                  throws FileNotFoundException,
                         IOException
Retrieves a file, specified by remotePath, from the ftp server and saves it locally to localPath.

Parameters:
remotePath - String, the remote path
localPath - String, the local path
Throws:
FileNotFoundException - - Thrown if the file exists but is a directory rather than a regular file, does not exist but cannot be created, or cannot be opened for any other reason.
IOException - - Thrown if an io error occurred saving the remotePath to localPath.
